{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VeUJEyruLis7W9KbM4JPyJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the key source files for the Obstruction2D-o4-v0 environment.\n\n## Summary: Obstruction2D-o4-v0 Environment Key Source Files\n\n### Directory Structure\n**Path:** `/robocode/prpl-mono/kinder/src/kinder/envs/geom2d/`\n\nKey files:\n- `base_env.py` - Base class for all Geom2D environments\n- `obstruction2d.py` - Obstruction2D-specific environment implementation\n- `object_types.py` - Type definitions for objects and robot\n- `utils.py` - Utilities including grasping logic and termination checks\n\n---\n\n### 1. **base_env.py** - Core Step Dynamics\n\n**Action Application:**\n- Actions are 5-tuples: `(dx, dy, dtheta, darm, vac)`\n- `dx, dy`: Relative position changes for robot base (clipped by action space)\n- `dtheta`: Relative rotation change (wrapped to [-π, π])\n- `darm`: Arm joint extension change (clipped between `base_radius` and `arm_length`)\n- `vac`: Absolute vacuum setting (0.0 = off, 1.0 = on)\n\n**Step() Dynamics (lines 139-197):**\n1. Update robot pose: x, y, theta, arm_joint, vacuum\n2. Get suctioned objects from previous timestep\n3. Snap suctioned objects to robot's new gripper position\n4. Move non-static objects in contact with suctioned objects\n5. Check collisions; revert state if any detected\n6. Return observation, reward, terminated flag, truncated flag, info\n\n**Collision Handling:**\n- Uses `state_2d_has_collision()` to check moving objects vs obstacles\n- Only applies state changes if no collisions detected (conservative approach)\n- Maintains static object body cache for efficiency\n\n**Key Constants (Obstruction2DEnvConfig defaults):**\n- `world_max_x` = golden ratio (≈ 1.618)\n- `world_max_y` = 1.0\n- `min/max_dx`: ±0.05\n- `min/max_dy`: ±0.05\n- `min/max_dtheta`: ±π/16\n- `min/max_darm`: ±0.1\n- `min/max_vac`: 0.0 to 1.0\n\n---\n\n### 2. **obstruction2d.py** - Environment-Specific Implementation\n\n**Reward & Termination:**\n- **Reward:** -1.0 at every step (penalty for time)\n- **Termination:** `is_on()` check returns True when target block is on target surface\n- Environment wraps the constant-object version for fixed numbers of obstructions\n\n**Scene Generation & Object Layout:**\n\n**Static Objects:**\n- **Table:** Base gray rectangle (width = world width, height = 0.1)\n- **Walls:** 4 boundary walls created from world coordinates\n\n**Dynamic Objects:**\n- **Robot (CRVRobotType):** \n  - Init pose: top-right area, facing down (θ = -π/2)\n  - base_radius = 0.1\n  - arm_length = 0.2 (2 × base_radius)\n  \n- **Target Block (TargetBlockType, movable):**\n  - Random size: width ∈ [0.05, 0.2], height ∈ [0.05, 0.2]\n  - Random x position on table surface\n  \n- **Target Surface (TargetSurfaceType, static on table):**\n  - Width = target_block_width + extra (extra ∈ [0.02, 0.05])\n  - Height = 0.1 (table height)\n  - Slightly larger than target block to provide placement surface\n  \n- **Obstructions (RectangleType, movable):**\n  - For Obstruction2D-o4: 4 obstruction objects\n  - Random size: width ∈ [0.05, 0.2], height ∈ [0.05, 0.2]\n  - 90% probability initialized ON the target surface (obstruction_init_on_target_prob = 0.9)\n  - 10% probability initialized elsewhere on table\n  \n**Sampling Constraints:**\n- Rejection sampling: up to 10,000 attempts\n- Invalid if: goal already satisfied, objects collide, or target surface outside table bounds\n- Objects clamped to stay within table margins\n\n---\n\n### 3. **object_types.py** - Type & Feature Definitions\n\n**CRVRobotType Features (9 features):**\n```\n\"x\", \"y\", \"theta\"              # SE(2) pose\n\"base_radius\"                   # Robot base circle radius\n\"arm_joint\"                     # Current arm extension (distance from base center to gripper)\n\"arm_length\"                    # Maximum arm extension\n\"vacuum\"                        # Vacuum setting (0.0 = off, ≥0.5 = on in practice)\n\"gripper_height\", \"gripper_width\"  # Gripper dimensions\n```\n\n**RectangleType Features (8 features):**\n```\n\"x\", \"y\", \"theta\"              # SE(2) pose\n\"width\", \"height\"              # Rectangle dimensions\n\"static\"                        # Boolean: 1.0 = static, 0.0 = movable\n\"color_r\", \"color_g\", \"color_b\"  # RGB color\n\"z_order\"                       # Collision layer (ZOrder.NONE, ZOrder.ALL)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **utils.py** - Vacuum Grasping & Termination\n\n**Vacuum Grasping (lines 183-208):**\n\n`get_suctioned_objects()` finds objects being grasped:\n1. Check if vacuum ≥ 0.5 (vacuum \"on\" threshold)\n2. Get gripper tool tip position (center of bottom edge of gripper rectangle)\n3. Build gripper-to-world transform\n4. Iterate movable objects; check if gripper suction geom intersects object geom\n5. For each intersecting object, compute gripper-to-object SE(2) transform\n6. Return list of (Object, SE2Pose) tuples representing grasp transforms\n\n`snap_suctioned_objects()` keeps grasped objects attached:\n- Each step, recomputes gripper position based on robot state\n- Updates suctioned object pose by: `world_obj = world_gripper * gripper_to_obj`\n- Maintains relative transform across timesteps\n\n**Termination Condition: `is_on()` (lines 327-349):**\n```python\ndef is_on(state, top, bottom, static_object_cache, tol=0.025):\n    # Checks if top object is completely on the bottom one\n    # For rectangles only\n    # Assumes \"up\" is positive y\n    \n    top_geom = rectangle_object_to_geom(state, top, static_object_cache)\n    bottom_geom = rectangle_object_to_geom(state, bottom, static_object_cache)\n    \n    # Get bottom-most vertices of top object\n    sorted_vertices = sorted(top_geom.vertices, key=lambda v: v[1])\n    \n    # Check if the 2 lowest vertices, offset down by tolerance (0.025),\n    # are contained within the botto