{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P3QXrhrUeavuUnSyUfMjPz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`rectangle_object_to_geom` is imported from `kinder.envs.utils` into `geom2d/utils.py` — the definition is in the parent module, which was already captured. Here is the complete summary of all requested functions:\n\n---\n\n## Results\n\nAll functions live in `/robocode/prpl-mono/kinder/src/kinder/envs/utils.py`. The `geom2d/utils.py` imports them and re-exports them.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `crv_robot_to_multibody2d` — where the CRV MultiBody2D is built\n\n```python\ndef crv_robot_to_multibody2d(obj: Object, state: ObjectCentricState) -> MultiBody2D:\n    bodies: list[Body2D] = []\n\n    # Base — a Circle at (base_x, base_y)\n    base_x = state.get(obj, \"x\")\n    base_y = state.get(obj, \"y\")\n    base_radius = state.get(obj, \"base_radius\")\n    circ = Circle(x=base_x, y=base_y, radius=base_radius)\n    base = Body2D(circ, ZOrder.ALL, ..., name=\"base\")\n    bodies.append(base)\n\n    # Gripper — a Rectangle centered at (gripper_cx, gripper_cy)\n    theta = state.get(obj, \"theta\")\n    arm_joint = state.get(obj, \"arm_joint\")\n    gripper_cx = base_x + np.cos(theta) * arm_joint\n    gripper_cy = base_y + np.sin(theta) * arm_joint\n    gripper_height = state.get(obj, \"gripper_height\")\n    gripper_width  = state.get(obj, \"gripper_width\")\n    rect = Rectangle.from_center(\n        center_x=gripper_cx, center_y=gripper_cy,\n        height=gripper_height, width=gripper_width,\n        rotation_about_center=theta,\n    )\n    gripper = Body2D(rect, ZOrder.SURFACE, ..., name=\"gripper\")\n    bodies.append(gripper)\n\n    # Arm — rectangle spanning base→gripper center, rotated theta+π/2\n    rect = Rectangle.from_center(\n        center_x=(base_x + gripper_cx) / 2,\n        center_y=(base_y + gripper_cy) / 2,\n        height=np.sqrt((base_x - gripper_cx)**2 + (base_y - gripper_cy)**2),\n        width=(0.5 * gripper_width),\n        rotation_about_center=(theta + np.pi / 2),\n    )\n    arm = Body2D(rect, ZOrder.SURFACE, ..., name=\"arm\")\n    bodies.append(arm)\n\n    # Suction (only when vacuum > 0.5) — rectangle beyond the gripper tip\n    if state.get(obj, \"vacuum\") > 0.5:\n        suction_height = gripper_height\n        suction_width  = gripper_width\n        suction_cx = base_x + np.cos(theta) * (arm_joint + gripper_width + suction_width / 2)\n        suction_cy = base_y + np.sin(theta) * (arm_joint + gripper_width + suction_width / 2)\n        rect = Rectangle.from_center(\n            center_x=suction_cx, center_y=suction_cy,\n            height=suction_height, width=suction_width,\n            rotation_about_center=theta,\n        )\n        suction = Body2D(rect, ZOrder.NONE, ..., name=\"suction\")\n        bodies.append(suction)\n\n    return MultiBody2D(obj.name, bodies)\n```\n\n**Key geometry:** The gripper center is at `(base_x + cos(theta)*arm_joint, base_y + sin(theta)*arm_joint)`. The gripper Rectangle is rotated by `theta`, so the arm extends outward along the heading direction.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `get_tool_tip_position`\n\n```python\ndef get_tool_tip_position(state, robot) -> tuple[float, float]:\n    \"\"\"Defined as the center of the bottom edge of the gripper.\"\"\"\n    multibody = crv_robot_to_multibody2d(robot, state)\n    gripper_geom = multibody.get_body(\"gripper\").geom  # Rectangle\n    tool_tip = np.array([1.0, 0.5])          # unit coords: right-center of rect\n    scale_matrix = np.array([[gripper_geom.width, 0], [0, gripper_geom.height]])\n    translate_vector = np.array([gripper_geom.x, gripper_geom.y])\n    tool_tip = tool_tip @ scale_matrix.T         # scale to actual size\n    tool_tip = tool_tip @ gripper_geom.rotation_matrix.T  # rotate by theta\n    tool_tip = translate_vector + tool_tip        # translate to world coords\n    return (tool_tip[0], tool_tip[1])\n```\n\nThe tip is the right/forward edge of the gripper rectangle (unit coord `[1.0, 0.5]` = full width, half height), transformed into world space via the gripper's own stored `(x, y)` origin and rotation matrix.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `get_suctioned_objects`\n\n```python\ndef get_suctioned_objects(state, robot) -> list[tuple[Object, SE2Pose]]:\n    \"\"\"Returns (object, gripper_to_obj transform) for every movable object\n    intersecting the suction body.\"\"\"\n    if state.get(robot, \"vacuum\") <= 0.5:\n        return []\n    robot_multibody = crv_robot_to_multibody2d(robot, state)\n    suction_body = robot_multibody.get_body(\"suction\")\n    gripper_x, gripper_y = get_tool_tip_position(state, robot)\n    gripper_theta = state.get(robot, \"theta\")\n    world_to_gripper = SE2Pose(gripper_x, gripper_y, gripper_theta)\n    movable_objects = [o for o in state if o != robot and state.get(o, \"static\") < 0.5]\n    suctioned_objects = []\n    for obj in movable_objects:\n        obj_multibody = object_to_multibody2d(obj, state, {})\n        for obj_body in obj_multibody.bodies:\n            if geom2ds_intersect(suction_body.geom, obj_body.geom):\n                world_to_obj = get_se2_pose(state, obj)\n                gripper_to_obj = world_to_gripper.inverse * world_to_obj\n                suctioned_objects.append((obj, gripper_to_obj))\n    return suctioned_objects\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `rectangle_object_to_geom` (defined in `kinder/envs/utils.py`, imported into `geom2d/utils.py`)\n\n```python\ndef rectangle_object_to_geom(state, rect_obj, static_object_cache) -> Rectangle:\n    assert (\n        rect_obj.is_instance(RectangleType)\n        or rect_obj.is_instance(DynRectangleType)\n        or rect_obj.is_instance(KinRectangleType)\n    )\n    multibody = object_to_multibody2d(rect_obj, state, static_object_cache)\n    assert len(multibody.bodies) == 1\n    geom = multibody.bodies[0].geom\n    assert isinstance(geom, Rectangle)\n    return geom\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary: Where is the gripper relative to `(robot_x, robot_y, theta, arm_joint)`?\n\nThe gripper **center** is:\n```\ngripper_cx = robot_x + cos(theta) * arm_joint\ngripper_cy = robot_y + sin(theta) * arm_joint\n```\n\nThe gripper rectangle is rotated by `theta` about its center. The **tool tip** (suction point) is the forward-facing edge of the gripper: one full `gripper_width` further along `theta` from the center:\n```\ntool_tip_x ≈ robot_x + cos(theta) * (arm_joint + gripper_width)\ntool_tip_y ≈ robot_y + sin(theta) * (arm_joint + gripper_width)\n```\n\nThe **suction zone** rectangle is centered yet another `gripper_width` further out (at distance `arm_joint + gripper_width + suction_width/2`)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a84d999f7f7ae380e (use SendMessage with to: 'a84d999f7f7ae380e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 18061\ntool_uses: 5\nduration_ms: 60110</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fa831d9-eb3f-4745-b971-234a10cba938","uuid":"b9c1e990-6bf5-4118-b7ec-960a261810e6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:10:34.830Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file /robocode/prpl-mono/kinder/src/kinder/envs/geom2d/utils.py and return:\n1. The full `object_to_multibody2d` function or wherever the CRV robot's MultiBody2D is constructed (arm, gripper, suction bodies)\n2. The `get_tool_tip_position` function (full body)\n3. The `get_suctioned_objects` function (full body)\n4. The `rectangle_object_to_geom` function\n\nFocus on understanding: where is the gripper relative to (robot_x, robot_y, theta, arm_joint)?\n\nUse /robocode/.venv/bin/python to run: \n```python\nimport kinder.envs.geom2d, os\npath = kinder.envs.geom2d.__path__[0]\nwith open(os.path.join(path, 'utils.py')) as f:\n    content = f.read()\n# Find relevant sections\nfor fn in ['object_to_multibody', 'crv_robot', 'CRVRobot', 'gripper', 'arm_joint', 'get_tool_tip', 'rectangle_object_to_geom']:\n    idx = content.find(fn)\n    if idx >= 0:\n        print(f\"\\n=== {fn} at {idx} ===\")\n        print(content[max(0,idx-50):idx+600])\n