{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   Write a complete behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0` — a 2D environment where a robot must place a target block onto a target surface that may be obstructed by 4 movable rectangular obstructions. The approach must use strictly separated files (obs_helpers.py, act_helpers.py, behaviors.py, approach.py), with no magic numbers in behaviors, and implement a fixed behavior sequence checked backwards from the last behavior's precondition.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - CRV Robot: circle base (radius=0.1), retractable arm (joint range [0.1, 0.2]), vacuum gripper\n   - Arm points in direction `theta`; arm points DOWN when theta=-π/2 (initial state)\n   - Suction center (theta=-π/2): `(robot_x, robot_y - arm_joint - SUCTION_OFFSET)` where SUCTION_OFFSET=0.015\n   - Suction zone when theta=-π/2: 0.07 wide in x (±0.035 around robot_x), only 0.01 tall in y (±0.005)\n   - Rectangle (x,y) in observation = BOTTOM-LEFT corner (not center)\n   - Objects on table: y≈0.1 (TABLE_TOP), center_y = y + h/2\n   - `is_on` termination: bottom 2 vertices of block offset by -0.025 must be inside surface rectangle\n   - Arm BODY spans from robot center to arm tip — collides with obstacles during downward extension\n   - Key formula: `arm_joint_target = robot_y - (obj_y + obj_height) - APPROACH_GAP (0.008)` ensures arm body clears obstruction top while suction zone intersects the obstruction\n   - Direct clipping controller (no proportional gain): `dx = clip(target - current, -max, max)` avoids oscillation\n   - Dynamic dump zone: search for x position where robot base (r=0.1) and carried object don't overlap any other objects\n   - ZOrder: ALL=100 (collides with everything), NONE=101 (no collision); target surface is ZOrder.NONE\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`/sandbox/obs_helpers.py`** — All observation parsing, indices, geometric predicates\n     - Constants: ROBOT_X=0..ROBOT_GRIPPER_WIDTH=8, SURF_X=9..SURF_HEIGHT=18, BLOCK_X=19..BLOCK_HEIGHT=28, OBS_BASE_INDICES=[29,39,49,59]\n     - Key functions: `extract_robot`, `extract_surface`, `extract_block`, `extract_obstruction`, `obstruction_on_surface`, `any_obstruction_on_surface`, `block_is_on_surface`, `find_clear_dump_x`\n     - `find_clear_dump_x(obs, carried_obs_idx, carried_w)`: scans world for clear dump position avoiding all other objects' x-ranges + robot base radius (0.1) + margin (0.015). Returns position farthest from surface.\n     - `block_is_on_surface`: checks both bottom-left and bottom-right vertices of block at (y - IS_ON_TOL=0.025) are inside surface rectangle\n\n   - **`/sandbox/act_helpers.py`** — All action generation, controllers, constants\n     ```python\n     ARM_MIN = 0.10; ARM_MAX = 0.20\n     SUCTION_OFFSET = 0.015  # gripper_width + suction_width/2\n     TABLE_TOP_Y = 0.10; CARRY_HEIGHT = 0.72\n     APPROACH_GAP = 0.008  # ensures arm body clears obj top when approaching from above\n     XY_TOL = 0.030; ARM_TOL = 0.005; CARRY_X_TOL = 0.03\n     TARGET_THETA = -np.pi / 2.0\n     \n     def move_action(rx, ry, rtheta, arm_joint, target_x, target_y, target_arm, vac):\n         dx = _clip(target_x - rx, -DX_MAX, DX_MAX)  # direct clipping, no gain\n         dy = _clip(target_y - ry, -DY_MAX, DY_MAX)\n         dtheta = _clip(_angle_diff(TARGET_THETA, rtheta) * THETA_GAIN, -DTHETA_MAX, DTHETA_MAX)\n         darm = _clip(target_arm - arm_joint, -DARM_MAX, DARM_MAX)  # no overshoot\n         return np.array([dx, dy, dtheta, darm, float(vac)], dtype=np.float64)\n     \n     def compute_pick_height(obj_height):\n         return TABLE_TOP_Y + obj_height / 2.0 + ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET\n     \n     def compute_arm_target(robot_y, obj_y, obj_height):\n         obj_top = obj_y + obj_height\n         target = robot_y - obj_top - APPROACH_GAP\n         return max(ARM_MIN, min(ARM_MAX, target))\n     ```\n\n   - **`/sandbox/behaviors.py`** — Three behavior classes\n     - `ClearSurface`: FIND→RETRACT→MOVE→EXTEND→GRASP→LIFT→RAISE→CARRY→DESCEND→LOWER→RELEASE→FIND loop\n       - Uses `compute_arm_target` for EXTEND (not ARM_MAX, to avoid collision with obstruction top)\n       - Uses `find_clear_dump_x` per obstruction (recomputed each pick, reset `_dump_x=None` after RELEASE)\n       - LOWER phase: extends to `self._arm_target` (same as EXTEND) so object lands at TABLE_TOP\n     - `PickBlock`: RETRACT→MOVE→EXTEND→GRASP; uses same `compute_arm_target`\n     - `PlaceBlock`: stores `self._arm_target = robot['arm_joint']` from PickBlock; LIFT→RAISE→CARRY→DESCEND→LOWER→RELEASE; places at `surf_cx = rect_center_x(surf)`\n\n   - **`/sandbox/approach.py`** — Thin GeneratedApproach class\n     ```python\n     def reset(self, state, info):\n         b_place = PlaceBlock(); b_pick = PickBlock(); b_clear = ClearSurface()\n         if b_place.initializable(state):  # vacuum=1\n             self._behaviors = deque([b_place])\n         elif b_pick.initializable(state):  # surface clear\n             self._behaviors = deque([b_pick, b_place])\n         else:\n             self._behaviors = deque([b_clear, b_pick, b_place])\n         self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n         self._current.reset(state)\n     ```\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **Oscillation in MOVE phase (XY_GAIN=2.5)**: Robot bounced between positions, never reaching target within tolerance. Fixed by switching from proportional control to direct clipping: `dx = clip(target - current, -max, max)`. Also increased XY_TOL from 0.018 to 0.030.\n   - **Arm won't extend (arm stays at 0.1)**: With ARM_GAIN=2.0 and error=0.046, da=0.092 which overshoots arm_target=0.146, making arm_joint jump to 0.192. At 0.192, arm body bottom = 0.386-0.192=0.194 < obs_top=0.222 → COLLISION → state reverted. Fixed by (a) computing arm_target via `compute_arm_target()` to stay above obstruction top, and (b) direct clipping for darm to prevent overshoot.\n   - **Fixed dump zone collision (seed 0)**: Original dump_x=1.368 overlapped with obs2's x-range [1.332, 1.487]. When descending with carried obs0 centered at 1.368, collision occurred at robot_y≈0.389 (above dump_pick_y=0.376). Fixed by implementing `find_clear_dump_x()` that searches for a clear x position.\n   - **ImportError**: `CARRY_X_TOL` not in act_helpers.py when first imported in behaviors.py. Fixed by adding the constant.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - **Approach from above vs side**: Tried to extend arm downward into obstruction from above, but arm body collides. Solved by computing `arm_joint_target` that keeps arm body ABOVE obstruction top while suction zone is just inside the top.\n   - **Landing height invariant**: When arm at `arm_joint_target` at `pick_y`, suction is at `obs_top - 0.007`. When object released at same configuration, it lands at `TABLE_TOP`. This symmetric pick/place height ensures objects land correctly.\n   - **Dynamic dump zones**: Fixed dump positions fail because other obstructions may be there. Implemented grid search for clear x position.\n   - **Progress as of last test**: Seeds 0, 2, 3 successfully clear surface and reach PickBlock.MOVE; seeds 1 (second obstruction issue) and 42 (EXTEND stuck) still failing; no seed yet reaches PlaceBlock.\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - Initial task message: Write behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0` with specific file structure requirements, no magic numbers, backward precondition checking in reset(), etc.\n   - \"CRITICAL: Respond with TEXT ONLY...\" — request for this summary\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Fix PickBlock.MOVE being stuck (seeds 0, 2, 3 reach here but time out)\n   - Fix ClearSurface.EXTEND stuck in seed 42 (arm still not extending)\n   - Fix ClearSurface stuck on second obstruction in seed 1\n   - Test PlaceBlock behavior (never reached yet)\n   - Verify full end-to-end success across all seeds\n   - Commit final working version\n\n8. Current Work:\n   Immediately before the summary request, the test output showed:\n   - Seed 0: surface_clear=True, vacuum=False, block_on_surf=False — stuck in PickBlock.MOVE\n   - Seed 1: surface_clear=False — stuck in ClearSurface on second obstruction\n   - Seed 2: surface_clear=True — stuck in PickBlock.MOVE\n   - Seed 3: surface_clear=True — stuck in PickBlock.MOVE\n   - Seed 42: surface_clear=False — stuck in ClearSurface.EXTEND\n\n   The last code change was implementing `find_clear_dump_x()` in obs_helpers.py and updating ClearSurface to use it per-obstruction (with `_dump_x=None` reset after RELEASE).\n\n   Current `behaviors.py` ClearSurface structure:\n   ```python\n   # In step(), after FIND:\n   ob = extract_obstruction(obs, self.current_obs_idx)\n   ob_cx = rect_center_x(ob)\n   pick_y = compute_pick_height(ob[\"height\"])\n   if self._dump_x is None:\n       self._dump_x = find_clear_dump_x(obs, self.current_obs_idx, ob[\"width\"])\n   dump_x = self._dump_x\n   arm_tgt = compute_arm_target(pick_y, ob[\"y\"], ob[\"height\"])\n   ```\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   The most recent failing issue is PickBlock stuck in MOVE (seeds 0, 2, 3). This is the same movement issue as before — the robot is likely failing to reach `(block_cx, pick_y)` due to collision with existing objects on the table (the robot base radius=0.1 colliding with obstructions that were dumped or the block itself).\n\n   Specifically: \"seed=0 step=91: PickBlock.MOVE ... Seed 0: TIMEOUT in 2000 steps, reward=-2000, surface_clear=True, vacuum=False, block_on_surf=False\"\n\n   Need to debug why PickBlock.MOVE gets stuck — likely the robot can't descend to pick_y because its base collides with table objects (either the block itself or remaining non-surface obstructions). Need to check: at the block's position, what is the maximum height of nearby objects that might block robot descent?\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/node/.claude/projects/-sandbox/4fa831d9-eb3f-4745-b971-234a10cba938.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4fa831d9-eb3f-4745-b971-234a10cba938","uuid":"b656015d-a9a8-41cb-a7ad-fb4ce74a2e06","timestamp":"2026-04-07T21:38:57.104Z","isSynthetic":true}
