{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user requested continuation of a session that was building a behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0`. The task: write a purely imperative, feedforward policy using a fixed sequence of behaviors (ClearSurface → PickBlock → PlaceBlock) to make a robot place a target block onto a target surface that may be obstructed by up to 4 movable rectangular obstructions. All code must use relative paths, no magic numbers, and behaviors must check preconditions backwards in reset(). The user's final message was a request for a conversation summary (\"CRITICAL: Respond with TEXT ONLY\").\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - CRV Robot: circle base (radius=0.100), retractable arm (joint [0.10, 0.20]), vacuum gripper pointing down (theta=-π/2)\n   - Suction center when theta=-π/2: `(robot_x, robot_y - arm_joint - SUCTION_OFFSET=0.015)`\n   - Suction zone: ±0.035 in x (SUCTION_HALF_X), ±0.005 in y (SUCTION_HALF_Y)\n   - Rectangle positions are BOTTOM-LEFT corner; objects rest at y=TABLE_TOP_Y=0.100\n   - Arm body: from robot center down to tip; arm tip = robot_y - arm_joint\n   - APPROACH_GAP=0.015: arm_tip = obj_top + 0.015 (clears neighbor tops)\n   - pick_y = TABLE_TOP + h/2 + ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET (standard formula)\n   - arm_tgt = robot_y - obj_top - APPROACH_GAP (clamped to [ARM_MIN, ARM_MAX])\n   - CARRY_HEIGHT=0.72: robot height when carrying objects above table\n   - Direct clipping controller: dx = clip(error, -max, max) — no overshoot\n   - `find_blocker_for`: circle-rect collision detection for robot base (radius=0.1) during descent\n   - Circle-rect collision: min_robot_y = ob_top + sqrt(R² - dx²) where dx = horizontal dist to nearest ob edge\n   - `compute_safe_pick_y`: uses SUCTION_HALF_X (0.035) check range to detect arm-blocking neighbors\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`/sandbox/act_helpers.py`**\n     - Changed APPROACH_GAP from 0.008 to 0.015\n     - Critical: fixes arm_tip collision with dumped neighbors (arm_tip = obj_top + 0.015 instead of 0.008)\n     - Landing height unchanged: APPROACH_GAP cancels in the formula ARM_MAX - h/2\n     ```python\n     APPROACH_GAP = 0.015     # clearance: arm_joint_target = robot_y - obj_top - APPROACH_GAP\n     ARM_MIN = 0.10; ARM_MAX = 0.20; CARRY_HEIGHT = 0.72\n     SUCTION_OFFSET = 0.015; SUCTION_HALF_X = 0.035; SUCTION_HALF_Y = 0.005\n     XY_TOL = 0.030; ARM_TOL = 0.005; CARRY_X_TOL = 0.03\n     ```\n\n   - **`/sandbox/obs_helpers.py`**\n     - Added `ROBOT_RADIUS = 0.100` constant (NOT used in compute_safe_pick_y)\n     - Added `find_blocker_for(obs, target_idx)` function\n     - `compute_safe_pick_y` kept using SUCTION_HALF_X (unchanged from working commit)\n     ```python\n     ROBOT_RADIUS = 0.100   # robot base radius (circle)\n\n     def find_blocker_for(obs, target_idx):\n         \"\"\"Find a non-surface obstruction that prevents robot from descending to pick_y.\"\"\"\n         ob_target = extract_obstruction(obs, target_idx)\n         target_cx = rect_center_x(ob_target)\n         pick_y = compute_safe_pick_y(obs, target_cx, ob_target[\"height\"], exclude_idx=target_idx)\n         best_blocker = None; best_top = -1.0\n         for i in range(NUM_OBSTRUCTIONS):\n             if i == target_idx: continue\n             if obstruction_on_surface(obs, i): continue  # handled by normal FIND\n             ob = extract_obstruction(obs, i)\n             ob_top = ob[\"y\"] + ob[\"height\"]\n             dx = max(0.0, max(ob[\"x\"] - target_cx, target_cx - (ob[\"x\"] + ob[\"width\"])))\n             if dx >= ROBOT_RADIUS: continue\n             min_robot_y = ob_top + (ROBOT_RADIUS**2 - dx**2) ** 0.5\n             if min_robot_y > pick_y:\n                 if ob_top > best_top:\n                     best_top = ob_top; best_blocker = i\n         return best_blocker\n     ```\n\n   - **`/sandbox/behaviors.py`**\n     - Phases: FIND→RETRACT→RISE→MOVE→DESCEND_PICK→EXTEND→GRASP→LIFT→RAISE→CARRY→DESCEND→LOWER→RELEASE→FIND\n     - RISE: raise to CARRY_HEIGHT at current x before horizontal movement (prevents diagonal collision with table objects)\n     - MOVE: horizontal movement at CARRY_HEIGHT\n     - DESCEND_PICK: lower from CARRY_HEIGHT to pick_y (clean vertical path)\n     - terminated(): `not any_obstruction_on_surface(obs) and not is_vacuum_on(obs)` (prevents early termination while carrying)\n     - FIND: picks tallest surface obstruction first; then checks find_blocker_for\n     - LOWER: uses `self._arm_target` (set at EXTEND time from pick_y, not dump_pick_y)\n     ```python\n     # FIND logic:\n     best_idx = None; best_top = -1.0\n     for i in range(NUM_OBSTRUCTIONS):\n         if obstruction_on_surface(obs, i):\n             ob_i = extract_obstruction(obs, i)\n             ob_top = ob_i[\"y\"] + ob_i[\"height\"]\n             if ob_top > best_top:\n                 best_top = ob_top; best_idx = i\n     # Check for non-surface path blocker\n     if best_idx is not None:\n         blocker = find_blocker_for(obs, best_idx)\n         if blocker is not None:\n             best_idx = blocker  # clear the blocker first\n     ```\n\n   - **`/sandbox/approach.py`** (unchanged from previous session):\n     ```python\n     class GeneratedApproach:\n         def reset(self, state, info):\n             b_place = PlaceBlock(); b_pick = PickBlock(); b_clear = ClearSurface()\n             if b_place.initializable(state): self._behaviors = deque([b_place])\n             elif b_pick.initializable(state): self._behaviors = deque([b_pick, b_place])\n             else: self._behaviors = deque([b_clear, b_pick, b_place])\n             self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n             self._current.reset(state)\n         def get_action(self, state):\n             if self._current.terminated(state) and self._behaviors:\n                 self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n                 self._current.reset(state)\n             return self._current.step(state)\n     ```\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **PickBlock.MOVE stuck (seeds 0,2,3) / ClearSurface.MOVE stuck (seed 1)**: Robot moved diagonally through floating obstructions or descended through tall dumped objects. Fixed by splitting MOVE into RISE (to CARRY_HEIGHT) + MOVE (horizontal) + DESCEND_PICK (vertical).\n   \n   - **ClearSurface.EXTEND stuck (seed 42)**: Neighbor obs3 (taller) blocked arm extension to target obs1. Fixed by picking tallest surface obstruction first in FIND loop.\n   \n   - **ClearSurface terminating early while carrying**: `terminated()` returned True when carried obstruction moved off surface x-range during CARRY. Fixed by adding `and not is_vacuum_on(obs)` to terminated().\n   \n   - **Seed 15 - arm_tip collision with dumped neighbor**: arm_tip = obs3_top + APPROACH_GAP = 0.183+0.008=0.191 = obs1_top. Physics reverted arm extension. Fixed by increasing APPROACH_GAP from 0.008 to 0.015.\n   \n   - **Seed 19 - robot base collision with initial non-surface obs2**: Robot at x=0.475 needed to descend to pick_y=0.352, but obs2 (NOT on surface) at x=[0.532,0.630], top=0.299 was physically adjacent (dx=0.057 < R=0.100). Circle collision at robot_y=0.381 > pick_y. compute_safe_pick_y missed it (SUCTION_HALF_X=0.035 check range didn't include obs2). Fixed by adding find_blocker_for() with circle-rect geometry, clearing obs2 first.\n   \n   - **Catastrophic failure from ba202d0 commit (changing compute_safe_pick_y to ROBOT_RADIUS + APPROACH_GAP=0.015)**: Raised pick_y for many seeds → arm_tgt became too large for dump_pick_y (lower) → in LOWER, arm tried to extend too far → placed objects below TABLE_TOP → physics reverted → all seeds failed. Root cause: pick_y ≠ dump_pick_y when pick_y raised; self._arm_target computed for raised pick_y fails at dump_pick_y. Fixed by: (a) reverting to 4f749cd state, (b) keeping compute_safe_pick_y with SUCTION_HALF_X (not ROBOT_RADIUS), (c) adding separate find_blocker_for for robot-base collision detection.\n   \n   - **b915b88 commit failed too**: Tried to fix LOWER by recomputing dump_arm_tgt = compute_arm_target(dump_pick_y, TABLE_TOP_Y, ob[\"height\"]). Still failed (1/25) because it was combined with the broken ROBOT_RADIUS expansion in compute_safe_pick_y from ba202d0.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully fixed seeds 0-19, 42, 100, 200, 999, 1234 (25/25 in test_more_seeds.py)\n   - Broader test (59 seeds): 56/59 passing; seeds 24, 46, 9999 still fail\n   - The key insight: pick_y raised by neighbors causes arm_tgt mismatch in LOWER if dump_pick_y < pick_y — must NOT raise pick_y via broader x-range check; instead detect and clear physical blockers separately\n   - Landing formula is independent of APPROACH_GAP: arm lands at TABLE_TOP regardless of APPROACH_GAP value (it cancels)\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - Initial task message (from previous session): Write behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0` with ClearSurface/PickBlock/PlaceBlock, no magic numbers, backward precondition checking\n   - \"CRITICAL: Respond with TEXT ONLY...\" — request for this summary (current session end)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Debug and fix seeds 24, 46, 9999 (from 59-seed broad test showing 56/59 passing)\n   - Potentially test on even more seeds to ensure robustness\n\n8. Current Work:\n   Immediately before the summary request, the broad 59-seed test was run showing:\n   ```\n   56/59 seeds succeeded\n   Failed seeds: [(24, 2000), (46, 2000), (9999, 2000)]\n   ```\n   The last git commit (61b68e4) had just been made: \"Fix seed 15/19: APPROACH_GAP=0.015; add find_blocker_for with circle-rect collision\". The 25-seed test (test_more_seeds.py) showed 25/25 passing. The broader test revealed 3 remaining failures.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Debug the 3 remaining