{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   Continue building a behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0`. Fix 3 failing seeds (24, 46, 9999) from the previous session, then iteratively fix all newly-discovered failures in a broad test suite. The system must use purely imperative, feedforward policies with behaviors: ClearSurface → PickBlock → PlaceBlock. All code in relative paths, no magic numbers, backward precondition checking in reset().\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - CRV Robot: circle base (radius=0.100), retractable arm (joint [0.10, 0.20]), vacuum gripper pointing down (theta=-π/2)\n   - Suction center when theta=-π/2: `(robot_x, robot_y - arm_joint - SUCTION_OFFSET=0.015)`\n   - SUCTION_HALF_X=0.035 (suction zone half-extent in x), SUCTION_HALF_Y=0.005 (in y)\n   - ARM_MIN=0.10, ARM_MAX=0.20, CARRY_HEIGHT=0.72, TABLE_TOP_Y=0.10\n   - APPROACH_GAP=0.015: arm_tgt = robot_y - obj_top - APPROACH_GAP\n   - arm_tip_y = target.top + APPROACH_GAP (constant, independent of pick_y)\n   - pick_y formula: `obj_y + obj_h/2 + ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET` (using actual obj_y, not TABLE_TOP)\n   - Stacking: when no clear dump_x, stack carried obs on top of non-block obstruction\n   - Circle-rect collision: `min_robot_y = ob_top + sqrt(R² - dx²)` where dx = horizontal dist to nearest x-edge\n   - arm_tgt formula: `robot_y - (obj_y + obj_h) - APPROACH_GAP` (clamped to [ARM_MIN, ARM_MAX])\n   - SURFACE_OVERLAP_MARGIN=0.0 (any x-overlap counts as \"on surface\")\n   - dump_floor_y: height of highest non-carried obs at dump_x (for stacking-aware placement)\n   - ARM BODY width: SUCTION_HALF_X (0.035) is the GRIPPER HEAD width (suction zone), NOT the arm stick width\n   \n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`/sandbox/obs_helpers.py`** (heavily modified):\n     - Added `get_floor_height_at(obs, dump_x, carried_idx, carried_half_w)`: returns max top among non-carried obs overlapping dump area (for stacking-aware dump height). Does NOT include block (to avoid stacking on block which creates collision issues during PickBlock.LIFT).\n     - Added `find_safe_pick_x(obs, ob, pick_y, exclude_idx=None)`: finds safe robot_x for picking (avoids circle-rect collision with all obs + block during descent). Checks from ob center, shifts left/right ±STEP within suction reach.\n     - Added `find_arm_blocker_for(obs, target_idx)`: finds non-surface obs that blocks arm extension. Uses SUCTION_HALF_X for overlap check (arm_lo/arm_hi = target_cx ± 0.035). Has regression issue – needs to be narrowed to only check obs that contain target_cx in their x-range.\n     - Added stacking fallback in `find_clear_dump_x`: when no clear dump_x found (dense search also fails), finds non-block, non-carried obs with lowest top where robot can descend to stacking height, returns its center as dump_x.\n     - Changed `SURFACE_OVERLAP_MARGIN` from 0.005 to 0.0.\n     - Added `target_y` parameter to `compute_safe_pick_y` (default=TABLE_TOP_Y). When target is stacked (y > TABLE_TOP), pick_y is correctly higher.\n     - Added `from act_helpers import ARM_MAX, SUCTION_OFFSET` inside `find_clear_dump_x`.\n\n   - **`/sandbox/behaviors.py`** (heavily modified):\n     - Added `SUCTION_OFFSET` to act_helpers imports.\n     - Added `find_arm_blocker_for, get_floor_height_at, find_safe_pick_x` to obs_helpers imports.\n     - ClearSurface.reset: added `self._pick_x = None` and `self._dump_floor_y = None`.\n     - ClearSurface.FIND: added reset of `_pick_x`, `_dump_floor_y`; calls `find_arm_blocker_for` after `find_blocker_for`.\n     - ClearSurface.step: computes `_pick_x` via `find_safe_pick_x`, computes `_pick_y` with `target_y=ob[\"y\"]`; computes `dump_floor_y` via `get_floor_height_at`; uses stacking-aware `dump_pick_y = dump_floor_y + ob[\"height\"]/2 + ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET`; RELEASE also resets `_pick_x` and `_dump_floor_y`.\n     - PickBlock: added `self._pick_x = None`; computes safe pick x via `find_safe_pick_x`.\n     \n   - **`/sandbox/approach.py`** (unchanged):\n     ```python\n     class GeneratedApproach:\n         def reset(self, state, info):\n             b_place = PlaceBlock(); b_pick = PickBlock(); b_clear = ClearSurface()\n             if b_place.initializable(state): self._behaviors = deque([b_place])\n             elif b_pick.initializable(state): self._behaviors = deque([b_pick, b_place])\n             else: self._behaviors = deque([b_clear, b_pick, b_place])\n             self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n             self._current.reset(state)\n         def get_action(self, state):\n             if self._current.terminated(state) and self._behaviors:\n                 self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n                 self._current.reset(state)\n             return self._current.step(state)\n     ```\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n\n   - **Seeds 24 & 46 stuck in ClearSurface.DESCEND**: Robot couldn't descend to dump_pick_y because previously-dumped objects stacked at dump_x blocked robot circle. Fix: stacking-aware dump_pick_y = dump_floor_y + h/2 + ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET where dump_floor_y = max top of obs at dump_x.\n\n   - **Seed 9999 stuck in ClearSurface.DESCEND_PICK**: Target BLOCK (h=0.198) physically blocked robot circle from descending to pick obs3 (dx=0.052 < R=0.100, min_robot_y=0.383 > pick_y=0.347). Fix: `find_safe_pick_x` shifts robot_x to avoid block collision while keeping suction in reach of obs.\n\n   - **Missing SUCTION_OFFSET import**: NameError in behaviors.py. Fix: added `SUCTION_OFFSET` to act_helpers import line.\n\n   - **Seed 52 stuck in ClearSurface.DESCEND (first attempt)**: `get_floor_height_at` didn't check the BLOCK at dump_x → dump_floor_y=0.100 even though block at dump_x=0.809. Attempted fix: include block in `get_floor_height_