{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HHrcRyjaCR7sUDoNUxppAX","type":"tool_result","content":"349\tdef find_clear_dump_x(obs, carried_obs_idx, carried_w):\n350\t    \"\"\"Find a dump x-position clear of all other objects.\n351\t\n352\t    Ensures robot base (radius=0.1) and carried obstruction (width=carried_w)\n353\t    centered at dump_x do not overlap any other object's x-range.\n354\t\n355\t    Searches left side first, then right side, starting from edges.\n356\t    Returns the best (farthest from surface) valid dump_x.\n357\t    \"\"\"\n358\t    import numpy as np\n359\t    from act_helpers import ARM_MAX, SUCTION_OFFSET\n360\t\n361\t    ROBOT_RADIUS = 0.1\n362\t    WORLD_MIN_X = 0.12\n363\t    WORLD_MAX_X = WORLD_WIDTH - 0.12\n364\t    MARGIN = 0.015  # extra clearance\n365\t\n366\t    # Half-width of exclusion zone around dump_x\n367\t    excl_hw = max(ROBOT_RADIUS, carried_w / 2.0) + MARGIN\n368\t\n369\t    # Collect all other objects' x-ranges to avoid\n370\t    other_ranges = []\n371\t    surf = extract_surface(obs)\n372\t    other_ranges.append((surf[\"x\"], surf[\"x\"] + surf[\"width\"]))  # avoid surface too\n373\t\n374\t    block = extract_block(obs)\n375\t    other_ranges.append((block[\"x\"], block[\"x\"] + block[\"width\"]))\n376\t\n377\t    for i in range(NUM_OBSTRUCTIONS):\n378\t        if i != carried_obs_idx:\n379\t            ob = extract_obstruction(obs, i)\n380\t            other_ranges.append((ob[\"x\"], ob[\"x\"] + ob[\"width\"]))\n381\t\n382\t    # Build blocked intervals for dump_x:\n383\t    # dump_x is blocked if it's within excl_hw of any other object\n384\t    blocked = [(ox - excl_hw, ox_r + excl_hw) for ox, ox_r in other_ranges]\n385\t\n386\t    def is_clear(x):\n387\t        return WORLD_MIN_X <= x <= WORLD_MAX_X and all(\n388\t            not (lo <= x <= hi) for lo, hi in blocked\n389\t        )\n390\t\n391\t    # Prefer side farther from surface center\n392\t    surf_cx = surf[\"x\"] + surf[\"width\"] / 2.0\n393\t    STEP = 0.04\n394\t\n395\t    # Search right side (high x) then left side\n396\t    candidates = []\n397\t    for x in np.arange(WORLD_MAX_X, WORLD_MIN_X - STEP, -STEP):\n398\t        if is_clear(x):\n399\t            candidates.append(x)\n400\t            break\n401\t    for x in np.arange(WORLD_MIN_X, WORLD_MAX_X + STEP, STEP):\n402\t        if is_clear(x):\n403\t            candidates.append(x)\n404\t            break\n405\t\n406\t    if not candidates:\n407\t        # Fallback: try denser search\n408\t        for x in np.arange(WORLD_MIN_X, WORLD_MAX_X, 0.01):\n409\t            if is_clear(x):\n410\t                return float(x)\n411\t        # Stacking fallback: find best non-block, non-carried obstruction to stack on.\n412\t        # Stack at center of obs with lowest top, checking other obs don't block descent.\n413\t        best_stack_x = None\n414\t        best_stack_top = float('inf')\n415\t        for i in range(NUM_OBSTRUCTIONS):\n416\t            if i == carried_obs_idx:\n417\t                continue\n418\t            ob_i = extract_obstruction(obs, i)\n419\t            stack_x = ob_i[\"x\"] + ob_i[\"width\"] / 2.0\n420\t            stack_top = ob_i[\"y\"] + ob_i[\"height\"]\n421\t            # Ensure other obstructions (not i, not carried) don't block descent here.\n422\t            # Approximate: use ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET above stack as pick height.\n423\t            approx_pick_y = stack_top + ARM_MAX + SUCTION_OFFSET + 0.10\n424\t            can_reach = True\n425\t            for j in range(NUM_OBSTRUCTIONS):\n426\t                if j == carried_obs_idx or j == i:\n427\t                    continue\n428\t                ob_j = extract_obstruction(obs, j)\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write